OL,3,C'The bank gave my family a #1 coin
OL,4,Cafter our father's death from infected
OL,5,Cblood'
OL,7,F"I had to take it. I couldn't throw it
OL,8,Fback but I had to take it because they
OL,9,Fhad to put something on the table and
OL,10,FI think it got a tin of beans and a
OL,11,Floaf of bread that we were able to
OL,12,Fmake last for a few days."
OL,14,FSpeaking ahead of the publication of
OL,15,Fthe final report of the infected blood
OL,16,Finquiry, the 47-year-old, from
OL,17,FBelfast, said: "He was a wonderful
OL,18,Fman, he was the life and soul of the
OL,19,Fparty.
